<TITLE> Cold snap spikes prices of vegetables </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 1 (bdnews24.com)The prices of vegetables have risen by as much as eight takas in the capital's retail markets over the last four days as the cold snap continues to affect the country. Dhaka's kitchen markets in Karwan Bazar, New Market, Mohammadpur and Shyamoli all registered significant price rises. The prices of vegetables have also shot up in the Bangladesh Rifles-run 'fair price shops', which are now retailing vegetables for almost the same price as the commercial markets. The price of a kilogram of beans is now Tk 14, up from Tk 10 last week, while green chilies have leapt to Tk 32 from, Tk 24 a few days ago. Mizanur Rahman, a customer at New Market, said: "The price of vegetables has been low up until now. But I am now shocked by the prices." Md Eskander, who runs a stall in Mohammadpur kitchen market, said: "Vegetable fields have been affected by the cold wave and rain over the last few days. The price of vegetables has risen due to the supply shortfall." bdnew
